<br>
Of course there are always exceptions to this rule.  If they are in the middle of a CR maybe it takes longer than 10 min (not applicable here as you mention no bodies) would be an example of an exception.  However, if they decide to leave the camp to do something, they can't put a page mark there (a pet in this case) and expect it back.  The lack of OOC reponse to camp checks and lack of activity for 10 min, IMHO, ends their claim to the camp.<br>
<br>
As far as how to deal with it...I think you did precisely the right thing.  Seriously, what are your options? <br>
<br>
1.  Try and out dick them for the camp.  Hotly contest the camp by trying to KS, train them etc.  Do that and you sink to their level IMHO.<br>
<br>
2. /petition for PnP.  Yeah...right.  Then everyone loses.  You have to deal with a guide parceling out the spawns as they happen until you each get half the xp and loot you would get if you owned that or a different camp, and likely to dissolve the second said guide wanders off.<br>
<br>
3.  Gracefully leave to another camp.  What you did and I think the best answer.  Avoid members of opposing group in future, do not aid, and go set up elsewere.  You had to deal with these jerks for maybe 10 minutes.  They have to deal with themselves their entire lives.  You will go on to make more friends, allies, connections, and see parts of the game they can only dream of.  They will be slowly sequestered and ostracized.  You went on to have fun at another location.  They got to keep a camp for a few hours.  I think the &quot;winner&quot; of this conflict is obvious.<br>
<br>
And because it's a question about camp contesting...I get to tell my favorite &quot;You stole my camp story&quot;!  Veterans of this board just go to the next post now, you've heard it before. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
